CNCP v1 24006
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#6400: Built-in macros need to be used outside a SFC ",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:25:49.845204+00:00",
  "text": "Built-in macros need to be used outside a SFC \n\n### What problem does this feature solve?\n\nCode simplicity & Code modularity & composition API usage boost\n\n### What does the proposed API look like?\n\n\r\nRoot elemnet \r\n\r\n```vue\r\n<template>\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div>\r\n        root\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <c1 v-model=\"value\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n</template>\r\n\r\n\r\n<script setup lang=\"ts\">\r\n\r\nimport c1 from './c1.vue'\r\n\r\nconst value = ref<string>('example')\r\n\r\n</script>\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nChidld 1\r\n\r\n```vue\r\n<template>\r\n\r\n    <div>\r\n        Child 1\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <c2 v-model=\"value\" />\r\n\r\n</template>\r\n\r\n<script setup lang=\"ts\">\r\n\r\nimport c2 from './c2.vue'\r\nimport { useComposuable } from './composuable'\r\n\r\nconst {\r\n    value\r\n} = useComposuable()\r\n\r\n\r\n</script>\r\n```\r\n\r\nChild 2\r\n\r\n```vue\r\n<template>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"\">\r\n\r\n        <div>\r\n            Child 2\r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        <input type=\"text\" v-model=\"value\">\r\n\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n</template>\r\n```\r\n\r\n```typescript\r\n<script setup lang=\"ts\">\r\n\r\nimport { useComposuable } from './composuable'\r\n\r\nconst {\r\n    value\r\n} = useComposuable()\r\n\r\n\r\n</script>\r\n```\r\n\r\nComposuable\r\n\r\n```typescript\r\nimport { defineProps, defineEmits } from \"vue\";\r\n\r\nexport function useComposuable() {\r\n\r\n    const props = defineProps<{\r\n        modelValue: string;\r\n    }>()\r\n\r\n    /*\r\n     * Emits\r\n     */\r\n    const emit = defineEmits<{\r\n        (e: 'update:modelValue', value: string): void\r\n    }>()\r\n\r\n    const value = computed<string>({\r\n        get: (): string => props.modelValue,\r\n        set: (value: string): void => emit('update:modelValue', value)\r\n    })\r\n\r\n    return {\r\n        props,\r\n        emit,\r\n        value\r\n    }\r\n\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n(yes, we can use provide/inject with computed value, but that may not be the ideal scenario every time.)",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":sparkles: feature request"
  ],
